'''Mohammad Ebrahim Bastani Parizi''' ({{lang-fa|محمد ابراهیم باستانی پاریزی}}, 12 December 1924 – 25 March 2014; born in [[Pariz]]) was an [[Iran]]ian historian, translator, poet, essayist and author of non-fiction books. His numerous publications (over 50 books) are mostly popular reads on topics such as the history of Iran and the history of his hometown [[Kerman]].<ref name="somebooks">{{cite web |url= http://www.ketabname.com/main2/lists/from_this_author.php?id=10-2-1-3&chlang=en|title= some books by M. E. Bastani Parizi (KetabNameh)|accessdate=2008-02-06 |work= some books by M. E. Bastani Parizi}}</ref><ref name="goodreads">[https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1350277 Mohammad Ebrahim Bastani Parizi] at [[Goodreads]]</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=November 2018|sure=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.majzooban.org/en/sufi-news/5391-mohammad-ebrahim-bastani-parizi-passes-away.html |title=Mohammad Ebrahim Bastani Parizi Passes Away |publisher=Majzooban.org |date=18 March 2014 |accessdate=2014-03-26}}</ref>

