{{notability|date=December 2012}}
'''Peter G. Rose''' (born 25 February 1939) is an American author and food historian.<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/1989/09/13/garden/a-food-historian-works-to-give-the-dutch-their-due.html</ref> She has published 8 books, mainly on the topic of food in colonial times, especially among the [[Dutch people|Dutch]] in the [[Hudson Valley]].
Peter Rose was born in [[Utrecht]], educated in the [[Netherlands]] and [[Switzerland]] and emigrated to the United States in 1964.
She received the Alice P. Kenney Award for her research and writing on the food customs and diet of the Dutch settlers in [[New Netherland]]. Through the [[New York Council for Humanities]] she has presented at the [[Smithsonian Institution]], the [[National Gallery of Art]] and the [[Culinary Institute of America]].<ref>http://www.nyhumanities.org/speakers/adult_audiences/speaker.php?speaker_id=278</ref>
