[[File:Bkksiamsociety090505a.jpg|thumb|The society's headquarters]]
The '''Siam Society Under Royal Patronage''' ({{lang-th|สยามสมาคมในพระบรมราชูปถัมภ์}}) is a society in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]], which aims to promote knowledge of Thailand. Its headquarters and library are on [[Asok Montri Road]] and it also runs the [[Kamthieng House Museum]]. It was founded on 26 February 1904 at a meeting at the Oriental Hotel.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|year=1904|title=The Foundation of the Society|url=http://www.siamese-heritage.org/jsspdf/1904/JSS_001_0j_FoundationOfTheSociety.pdf|journal=Journal of the Siam Society|volume=1|pages=|via=}}</ref>

{{Quote|text=The first resolution proposed was to the effect that those there assembled should form themselves into a society for research and investigation in matters appertaining to Siam.|sign=|source=}}

There were 103 founding members,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|year=1904|title=Report for 1904|url=http://www.siamese-heritage.org/jsspdf/1904/JSS_001_0l_ReportFor1904.pdf|journal=Journal of the Siam Society|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> and currently the society has close to 1800 members.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.siam-society.org/about/milestones.html|title=Siam Society - Milestones|website=www.siam-society.org|access-date=2016-12-10}}</ref> The society has published the ''[[Journal of the Siam Society]]'' (JSS) since 1904 and the articles aged over a hundred years are available online.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/tech/computer/301595/siam-society-journal-now-available-to-all|title=Siam Society: 108 years now online|last=|first=|date=2012-07-09|work=|newspaper=Bangkok Post|access-date=2016-12-10|via=}}</ref> The proceedings of the society were submitted to UNESCO's [[Memory of the World Programme]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unesco.org/new/en/communication-and-information/flagship-project-activities/memory-of-the-world/register/full-list-of-registered-heritage/registered-heritage-page-8/the-minute-books-of-the-council-of-the-siam-society-100-years-of-recording-international-cooperation-in-research-and-the-dissemination-of-knowledge-in-the-arts-and-sciences/|title="The Minute Books of the Council of the Siam Society", 100 years of recording international cooperation in research and the dissemination of knowledge in the arts and sciences {{!}} United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization|website=www.unesco.org|access-date=2016-12-10}}</ref>

